page.title: 09PEBBLES,SHELLS,SEA BIRDS.
page.content: At Chapel Point you can find a variety of pebbles,fossils and shells,many of which have come from Durham,Scotland,and Scandinvia.We've found a pink Granite,Gneiss,Blue stones,Mill stones,Grit,Limestone,Chalk quartz,and Flint.Many of the flints found at Chapel Point have been used by man as axe heads.Some stones are semi-precious like Amber,Agate,and Jet.The Fossils are bullet like bellennites,curly,ammonites,devils toenails and bivlave shells.Shells such as welk,scallop,razor,cockles,screw and wedge,sunset,angels wings are common.Along the beaches, common gulls,black headed gulls,guillemots,common terns,dunlins and ringed plovers can be seen.
